reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Hands down, favorite packing necessity!
reviews.reviewText: LOVE these — first, the pink is perfect… a beautiful soft pink with light and dark grey at the zippers. The material - I was expecting neoprene (now I can’t remember exactly what it felt like) - it was a great high quality material, that stretches a bit… SUPER strong zipper and I love the compression feature. They hold a lot! And then you can zip up the compression zipper so it takes up less space. We received an email from the company with tips on how to use — which was helpful. I don’t think the zipper would break either way, but it made it easier to zip up the packing cube (which we had really stuffed!).I was actually EXCITED using these because they were so beautiful, high quality, and hold a lot!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I bought several different brands for a trip to Europe. These were my absolute favorite. Strong, lightweight, with handles to pull them out of the suitcase. They did a great job

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars I like them
reviews.reviewText: Well made, very sturdy zippers I use regular packing cubes & thought I'd give the compression a try for an upcoming vacation. Did a trial packing & they do save a bit more space. I am an older gal with arthritis in fingers/hands so zipping took awhile. They work great as long as you don't stuff them too full.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These packing cubes are fantastic!
reviews.reviewText: I am so glad I got these!I got them for a two-week overseas trip and they were rock stars! Worth every penny. They could be overstuffed and all the zippers still worked smoothly. The compression feature allowed me to overpack :) and still get everything neatly tucked into my suitcase. My only wish is that they had a pocket with a clear window so I could have labeled what was in each cube.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Compression is the way to go!
reviews.reviewText: I've used these now on various trips and must say that I'm a convert even though you will need to iron out clothing that is not wrinkle proof/resistant.Overall, a great product that does save space allowing you to maximize your luggage's real estate. If you have not tried compression packing, I would recommend you do. It gets the job done and makes it easy to get organized when travelling!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality, lightweight
reviews.reviewText: These are my first compression cubes and I’m impressed. The product quality is high and the materials are lightweight and feel like good quality. I am on my first international trip with these packs and have no complaints so far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Does Not Save Any Space in Suitcase
reviews.reviewText: Perhaps my expectations were not as they should be, but I thought that by purchasing "compression" cubes, I would actually be able to put items in the cubes and compress them down so that they took up less space in my suitcase. Not the case with these bags.I actually read all the online reviews for countless compression bags before ordering these. Not only that, but I did a search for Best Compression Packing Cubes 2023 and read three different articles, all of which highly recommended these Gonex Compression Packing Cubes. One of the reviews I read was from a lady who'd packed ten pairs of jeans in the large bag. So when I received mine I rolled up ten pairs of jeans and tried putting them in the large bag. Yes, they did fit, but they did not compress even the slightest bit. In fact, the second zipper that's supposed to "compress" the contents would barely zip and even after it was zipped, the bag was the same size it was originally although a slightly different shape.I will say that the bags appear to be well made. They were lightweight material yet seems to be sturdy. The zippers seemed good quality. As I mentioned, I was able to get ten pairs of rolled up jeans (size 8) in the large bag, but no space saved. These would be excellent for someone only looking to organize their suitcase, but if you truly want to compress items, I can't recommend these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Smaller size allows greater packing flexability
reviews.reviewText: I was used to using more cube shaped packing cubes. Always ran into issues when trying to arrange in a suitcase. These, being a bit narrower and smaller allowed for a better arrangement in my bag. I was able to get 4 days of clothes in 3 of the cubes. Using the largest for my shirts. skipping the next size down. 2pr jeans and 2 pr of tech pants in the next cube and undies in the smallest. Worked perfect. Might order another set to lend to greater flexibility for packing. I was a little concerned that when using compression zipper, I was going to ruin the zipper, due to the bulk of the clothes in the cube. I took my time to zip, tucking in the cube fabric and clothes so the zipper didnt bind. Would like to see the zipper a bit more reinforced, but over all product works well.

reviews.reviewTitle: Excellent quality: lightweight fabric, zippers, stitching, handles! Compression feature is A+
reviews.reviewText: I ordered the purple Gonex compression cubes set (first time purchase from Gonex). The package arrived very fast. I am extremely happy with this purchase! & highly recommend! The quality of the compression cubes is excellent: lightweight beautiul fabric, including true colour, quality zippers & stitching, quality handles on all the compression cubes. The cubes compress very well. I wanted this feature to maximize my luggage space for future travel. The cube set fits perfectly into a carry-on size suitcase. I read in some reviews that the zipper is not good quality. This is not true. I will buy more sets as gifts in the near future. If you are thinking of purchasing compression cubes, you will not be disappointed with these!

These packing cubes are excellent. My first purchase of this type of product, I decided to go for one with good reviews and not necessarily the cheapest. My research showed that the compression ones were worth getting. These are good quality, good sizes and for the first time EVER I did a three-night interstate trip with hand luggage only. I am a convert.

These compression bags work really well. They compress your packing to create additional space in luggage, keep everything neat, tidy and accessible and the clothes come out less wrinkled than with conventional packing. Sometimes they can be a little hard to zip up at first but once you develop the technique you'll never go back. I wouldn't travel without them now.
Bags open up and then when you use double zips they compress the contents makes for a tidy suitcase/bag wish they had a label area so you know what’s what

I went backpacking across south east asia for two months and brought these along with me. These things were a life saver for organization and space conservation.The compression part is kind of a gimmick, you don't really need the second zipper to compress your clothes but it does help a bit. I found just opening the main zipper and shoving stuff in worked well enough. If you really needed a bit more compression than the second zipper is great you just have to be careful when zipping it back up for compression purposes because the zipper will get caught in the fabric and you might rip the zipper off if you're not being a little careful.I do take care of my things well, either way these are fairly cheap and still look brand new after two months of heavy usage.
